  • Package org.opengis.example.geometry

    • Class SimpleDirectPosition extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      5075669833975740957L

      • Serialized Fields

        • crs

          CoordinateReferenceSystem crs
          The coordinate reference system associated to this direct position, or null if unspecified.

          The SimpleDirectPosition class does not provide any setter for this field, since uncontrolled modifications of geometry CRS is often undesirable. The decision to allow modifications or not is left to subclasses.

          See Also:
          SimpleDirectPosition.getCoordinateReferenceSystem()

        • ordinates

          double[] ordinates
          The ordinate values. The length of this array is the dimension of this direct position.

          This array is public for allowing more efficient ordinates operations, for example using the Arrays methods. However we encourage to use only the methods from the DirectPosition interface in most cases.

          See Also:
          SimpleDirectPosition.getCoordinate()

    • Class SimpleEnvelope extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -6248863166463143789L

      • Serialized Fields

        • crs

          CoordinateReferenceSystem crs
          The coordinate reference system associated to this envelope, or null if unspecified.
          See Also:
          SimpleEnvelope.getCoordinateReferenceSystem()

        • ordinates

          double[] ordinates
          Ordinate values of lower and upper corners. The length of this array is twice the number of dimensions. The first half contains the lower corner, while the second half contains the upper corner.

      • Serialized Fields

        • eastBoundLongitude

          double eastBoundLongitude
          The eastern-most coordinate of the limit of the dataset extent. The value is expressed in longitude in decimal degrees (positive east).

        • northBoundLatitude

          The northern-most, coordinate of the limit of the dataset extent. The value is expressed in latitude in decimal degrees (positive north).

  • Package org.opengis.example.parameter

    • Class SimpleParameter extends SimpleIdentifiedObject implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -127301955366750847L

      • Serialized Fields

        • type

          SimpleParameter.Type type
          The parameter type, which determines the range of values and the unit of measurement. This field can be null if the parameter type is none of the enumerated ones.

        • value

          double value
          The parameter value. This is the only mutable property of the SimpleParameter class.
          See Also:
          SimpleParameter.doubleValue(), SimpleParameter.setValue(double)

    • Class SimpleParameterGroup extends SimpleIdentifiedObject implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -6759063712059101098L

      • Serialized Fields

        • parameters

          List<SimpleParameter> parameters
          The list of parameters included in this group. This simple group implementation supports only SimpleParameter instances, which are used both as parameter descriptor and parameter values for the double value type.

          This list is live: changes to this list will be reflected immediately in the SimpleParameterGroup.descriptors() and SimpleParameterGroup.values() views.

        • unmodifiable

          List<SimpleParameter> unmodifiable
          An unmodifiable view over the SimpleParameterGroup.parameters list. This view is returned by the SimpleParameterGroup.descriptors() and SimpleParameterGroup.values() methods. We have to make it unmodifiable for type safety reason.

  • Package org.opengis.example.referencing

    • Class AffineTransform2D extends AffineTransform implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -2450159714021625517L

      • Serialized Fields

        • inverse

          AffineTransform2D inverse
          The inverse of this affine transform, or null if not yet computed. Note that this field is part of the serialization; we do not declare it as transient even if we could easily recompute it, because if the user serialize the inverse transform rather than the original transform, then inverting the inverse transform in order to get back the original transform would lead to floating point errors.

  • Package org.opengis.example.util

    • Class SimpleName extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      5767162955069918493L

      • Serialized Fields

        • name

          Name name
          The JNDI name wrapped by this SimpleName. While JNDI names are mutable, GenericName are expected to be immutable. Consequently users are advised to not modify this object.
          See Also:
          SimpleName.jndiName()

        • scope

          SimpleNameSpace scope
          The scope (name space) in which this name is local. The scope is set on creation and is not modifiable. The scope of a name determines where a name starts.

          This field shall not be null, except for the global namespace.

          See Also:
          SimpleName.scope()
